**6a.** The formula for the present value annuity with *C* as the dollars per period and *r* as the rate is given as:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value annuity}&=\text{C}\times\dfrac{1-\frac{1}{(1+\text{r})^\text{time}}}{\text{r}}
\end{aligned}$$

For the future value annuity, the formula is:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Future value annuity}&=\text{C}\times\dfrac{(1+\text{r})^\text{time}-1}{\text{r}}
\end{aligned}$$

**6b.** The present value of a perpetuity refers to the present value of a payment that is done with no time constraints. This means that the payment goes on, ideally, forever. This can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value of perpetuity}&=\dfrac{\text{C}}{\text{r}}
\end{aligned}$$
